==English==

===Etymology===
Probably onamotopoetic. The second definition may come from the Nerf brand of toys, which are foam and inneficiant, and when something in a game is made weak, or like foam, it has been nerfed.

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{cattag|auto racing}} To bump lightly, whether accidentally or purposefully.
#: ''A racer will often nerf another as a psychological tactic.''
# {{slang}} to [[weaken]], [[water down]], or [[dumb down]]
#:''The lightning spell was pretty powerful before they '''nerfed''' it.''

